The article is a transcript of a press gaggle by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs aboard Air Force One en route to Louisiana. Gibbs discusses the schedule for the trip, including meetings with various government officials and local leaders. He also mentions the President's visit to Grand Isle to meet with locals and small business owners affected by the oil spill. Gibbs provides updates on the progress of the riser package and mentions the President's decision to cancel his trip to Indonesia and Australia. He explains that the President wants to come down to Louisiana to hear directly from those impacted by the spill and to get a firsthand account of the response efforts. Gibbs also mentions discussions with Israel regarding international participation in the investigation of the Israel flotilla situation.